    <h1> Medical Errors in the U.S.</h1>
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-!2 col-sm-12">
    <p>Healthcare Associated Infections are the third leading cause of death in the United States. In 2013, the government took a look at the numbers each hospital reported and reduced the funding of the top 25% of hospitals by 1%.
    
    As a result to the high number of medical errors, training methods are being implemented to reduce these numbers, but will it ever be enough?
    In the visuals below you can see how many hospitals were punished per state, and use the map to see if you home hospital was one of them.
    Also, take a look at the video below to see what medical experts have to say about TeamSTEPPS, one of the educational methods being implemented in efforts to reduce the communication breakdowns that occur in the surgical units.</p>
   </div>
    
